Program 4.3	
Write 	a JS program to demonstrate the use of constructor.
Code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<head>
</head>
<body>
<script>
class student {
constructor(name,age){
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;}} 
var s1 = new student("Astha",17);
var s2 = new student("",18);
  document.write("Name: " + s1.name + "<br>");
  document.write("Age: " + s1.age + "<br>");
  document.write("Name: " + s2.name + "<br>");
  document.write("Age: " + s2.age );
</script> 
 </body>
</html>


Program 4.4
Write 	a JS program to demonstrate the concept of message passing.
Code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<head>
</head>
<body>
    <script>
        class Id1 {
            add() {
                document.write("Addition Method Called");
            }}
